      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2021-03-18</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2021-05-06T13:10:47Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>School Reopening and Spending Transparency Act</strong></p> <p>This bill requires the Department of Education to establish and update monthly a public website to track state expenditures of certain COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019) education relief funds. States must report on the operating status of their public elementary and secondary schools during the 2020-2021 school year for inclusion on the website. </p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
